This paper discusses the issue of patient privacy and the potential for re-identification of patient records using publicly available data. This topic falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves the protection of sensitive information and the retrieval of relevant data. Additionally, the use of databases and data mining techniques is relevant to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the focus on patient demographics and medical information suggests that the sub-category of computational biology (cs.CY) may also be relevant.
